description:
## Severity
Trivial
## Dimension
error-handling
## Location
src/plugins/manager.rs:29-47
## Violation
If `dirs::home_dir()` returns None (sandboxed environments, missing $HOME), the manager initialises with ONLY the project plugins dir, no warning, no log. Quoted lines:

    pub fn new() -> Self {
        let mut search_paths = Vec::new();
        if let Some(home) = dirs::home_dir() {
            search_paths.push(home.join(".openclaudia").join("plugins"));
            search_paths.push(home.join(".claude").join("plugins"));
        }
        search_paths.push(PathBuf::from(".openclaudia/plugins"));
        ...
    }

A user wondering why their `~/.claude/plugins/foo` isn't loading gets zero signal. InstalledPlugins::load also silently degrades because its file_path falls back to a relative path. Same pattern as marketplaces_dir (line 263-268) which falls back to `.` — meaning marketplaces could land in cwd.
## Mandated refactor
Emit a `warn!` (or `error!` if managed-policy mode is detected) when home_dir returns None. Make PluginManager::new return Result<Self, PluginError> and let install_from_marketplace return an error if HOME is unset — silent degradation here is worse than fail-fast.
